 of success and shows how students, teachers and parents navigate the everyday demands of Dreamfields’ results-driven conveyor belt. Hopes and dreams are effectively harnessed and mobilized to enact insidious forms of social control, as education develops new sites and discourses of surveillance.This book is relevant to United Nations Sustainable Development Goal 4, Quality education  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aDreamfields Academy.  aQuality education.  aclassed inequalities.  acomprehensive education.  ademocratic accountability.  aeducation centralization.  aeducation marketization.  aethnic minorities.  agendered inequalities.  agentrification.  alabour conditions.  aneoliberal education.  aneoliberal governance.  apoverty.  araced inequalities.  aurbanderry.1 aKulz, Christy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packagez978311128281740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611618540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526116185423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526116185/original  a978-3-11-128281-7  Manchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packageb2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles